Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.21,0:26:26.64,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,他写道 我过去就是这样一个荡树的孩子\N{\fscx070\fscy070}He wrote,"So I was once myself a swinger of birches,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.01,0:26:30.74,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,而现在我总是梦想着回到过去\N{\fscx070\fscy070}and so I dream of going back to be."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.85,0:26:35.79,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我也是 Frost先生\N{\fscx070\fscy070}So do I,Mr. Frost.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.85,0:26:38.05,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我也想回到过去\N{\fscx070\fscy070}So do I.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.37,0:26:57.17,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,去吃饭吧 你准备好没\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Let's go. You ready?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.24,0:27:00.64,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我不饿\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I'm not hungry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.65,0:27:09.92,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我们快准备好了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}We'll be right up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.96,0:27:16.83,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,你不觉得这些家人对你很友好吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}These folks are being very gracious,don't you think?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.89,0:27:20.49,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,在那么发生多事情后还让你到他们家住\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Inviting you to their home after everything that's happened.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.56,0:27:23.90,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,拜托 我是来工作的 我有活要干\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Look. I come to work. I do my job. Okay?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.97,0:27:28.00,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我就答应做这些而已 我的保释书上可没写\N{\fscx070\fscy070}That's the deal I made. My probation doesn't say anything...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.07,0:27:31.51,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,要我必须跟他们排排坐吃果果\N{\fscx070\fscy070}about me sittin' around spittin' out watermelon seeds with you people.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.58,0:27:32.83,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我敢说 孩子\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I gotta tell you,son. {\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.83,0:27:36.15,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以你这种心态在这里熬不过一个暑假\N{\fscx070\fscy070} I don't think you're gonna make the summer with this attitude.{\r}
