Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.60,0:35:49.51,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,看你能得多少分 射门手\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Let's see what you got,slugger.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.57,0:35:51.34,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.93,0:36:10.79,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,哦 击中一球了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Oh,there's a shot!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.86,0:36:14.42,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,本垒打 - 那才不是我最好的一垒\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- It's a home run! - That wasn't my best pitch.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.50,0:36:18.66,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,- 其实棒球不是我的菜 -那是\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- Baseball's not really my sport. - What is?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.74,0:36:20.67,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,- 田径 - 不是吧\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- Track. - Really?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.74,0:36:23.37,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,跨栏 我以前挺擅长的 但是现在\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Running hurdles. I was pretty good,but then...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.44,0:36:26.47,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,把你的膝盖摔碎后这一切很快都改变了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}cracking your kneecap will change that one in a hurry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.54,0:36:29.31,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,真可惜\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Ouch. Yeah.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.38,0:36:32.37,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,以前还得过波士顿大学的全额奖学金\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I had a full ride to B.U.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.45,0:36:34.94,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,现在只能用老方法去支付大学费用\N{\fscx070\fscy070}So I'll just have to pay for college the old-fashioned way now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.02,0:36:37.51,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,像学生贷款\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Student loans.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.72,0:36:41.59,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,大学后呢\N{\fscx070\fscy070}What's after college?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.66,0:36:43.59,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,也许会学医\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Probably med school.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.86,0:36:49.13,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,虽然有时候我会有些不实际的想法\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Although I'd like to toy with the idea...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.20,0:36:52.23,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,像是一辈子就这里的树林里写写诗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}of spending my whole life here in the woods,writing poetry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.30,0:36:56.43,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,是啊 学医听起来更实际些\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Yeah. Med school sounds a bit more practical.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.48,0:37:03.88,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,有些事听起来比在桦树上荡树枝还糟糕\N{\fscx070\fscy070}There are worse things to be than a swinger of birches.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.22,0:37:07.15,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,你知道那首诗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}You know that poem?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.65,0:37:11.09,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我的最爱\N{\fscx070\fscy070}My favorite.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.22,0:37:15.39,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我听到你的演说了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I heard your speech.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.63,0:37:18.56,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,什么\N{\fscx070\fscy070}What?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.23,0:37:26.80,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我看到你在漫步 然后你就跟着我了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I saw you walking. And you followed me?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.17,0:37:32.87,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢你的演讲 说真的\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I liked it. Honest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.38,0:37:38.51,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,虽然那首诗挺让人伤感的 是吧\N{\fscx070\fscy070}It's a sad poem too,though,isn't it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.38,0:37:42.53,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,生活是一片迷失的森林 \N{\fscx070\fscy070}Life is too much like a pathless wood .{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.53,0:37:47.63,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让你的脸又痛又痒\N{\fscx070\fscy070} where your face burns and tickles.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.63,0:37:51.08,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,当你撞上了蜘蛛网\N{\fscx070\fscy070}The cobwebs,broken across it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.16,0:37:55.66,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,忽然一只眼又流泪 因为树枝在它睁开抽了它\N{\fscx070\fscy070}And one eye is weeping from having a twig lash across.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.73,0:37:59.76,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我更愿意逃离地球一小会儿\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I'd like to get away from Earth a while,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.84,0:38:03.03,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,然后再回来重新开始\N{\fscx070\fscy070}and then come back to it and begin over.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.89,0:38:22.42,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,你在想什么\N{\fscx070\fscy070}What are you thinking?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.49,0:38:23.73,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我在想\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I was just thinking about that .{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.73,0:38:28.90,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你那天带给我的那个三明治\N{\fscx070\fscy070} ham sandwich you brought me the other day.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.90,0:38:31.27,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,好吃吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}What about it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.34,0:38:34.70,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,如果再有芥末酱 或者是\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I was just wondering if there was mustard,or...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.26,0:39:02.79,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,-刚才感觉很好 - 只是很好吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- That was nice. - Nice?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.87,0:39:06.27,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,很多事情都会变得美好起来-比如说\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- There was a lot going on in "nice." - Like what?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.93,0:39:34.19,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,- 我该给它起什么名 -他应该叫米奇\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- What name should I give him? - His name should be Mikey.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.27,0:39:39.64,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,-Mikey Red怎样-不错\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- How about Mikey Red? - Mikey Red is a very good name.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.70,0:39:42.83,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,妈 这个怎样\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Mom. What about this one?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.91,0:39:44.84,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,啊 这个还好 没有太大惊喜\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Ah,it's okay. It doesn't thrill me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.91,0:39:47.71,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,妈咪 妈咪 我想尿尿\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Mom. Mommy,I have to go tinkle.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.78,0:39:50.51,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,没事 我带她去\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I'll take her. It's all right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.58,0:39:52.52,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,- 多谢了 老妈 - 没事\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- Thanks,Mom. - Okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.09,0:40:01.49,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,你在干嘛 老盯着我看 -哼哼\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- What,already? You keep staring at me. - Mm-hmm.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.56,0:40:04.49,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,你一直在跟他见面 对不对\N{\fscx070\fscy070}You're seeing him,aren't you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.16,0:40:10.07,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,-跟谁 -别跟我装蒜\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- Who? - Don't even think about denying it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.13,0:40:13.26,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我知道这个表情 Sam 我也有过这个表情\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I know that look,Sam. I have had that look.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.34,0:40:16.86,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我们就是一起玩玩而已 没什么大不了的\N{\fscx070\fscy070}We just hung out. No big deal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.94,0:40:20.14,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,你疯了吗 你了解Rallston的家伙吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Are you crazy? You know what those Rallston guys are like.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.21,0:40:22.15,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,不知道 不过我知道你认识那些是啥样的\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- No. I know what your Rallston guy was like. - Excuse me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.21,0:40:25.27,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,相信我  他们都是一个德行\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Trust me. They are all the same.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.35,0:40:27.28,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得我不知道你在想什么吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}You don't think I know what you're feeling?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.35,0:40:31.79,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,他对你来说刺激 出挑 小危险的诱惑是么\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Hmm? He seems exciting to you,different,maybe even a little dangerous.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.86,0:40:34.88,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,但是相信我 亲爱的 我经历过这些\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Believe me,honey. I have been there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.59,0:40:40.50,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我又不跟他结婚 简 我们只是 -玩玩而已\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- I'm not marrying him,Jen. We're just... - Hanging out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.87,0:40:45.43,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,是吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.50,0:40:47.44,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.97,0:41:21.94,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,咦 我们不是过会儿才见面吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Hey. I thought we were gonna meet later.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.01,0:41:25.13,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 看到你走进来就有些情不自禁了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Well,when I saw you walk in,I couldn't wait.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.21,0:41:28.70,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我跟 Malcolm说我走路回家了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I told Malcolm I was walking home.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.78,0:41:32.58,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,你兄弟Pete在这里 - 是啊 我知道\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- Your,uh,good buddy Pete's up there. - Yeah,I know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.65,0:41:35.24,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,难道我就不能买瓶汽水吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}So I can't buy a soda?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.42,0:41:41.48,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,- 过来 -你想做什么\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- Come here. - What are you doing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.50,0:41:49.97,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,嘿 宝贝儿\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Hey,baby.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.24,0:42:02.18,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,Vanessa 看我发现了什么\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Hey,Vanessa. Look what we got here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.25,0:42:05.44,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,-Sam你在做什么 - 没 什么也没做\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- Sam,what are you doing? - Nothing. I'm not doing anything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.52,0:42:09.45,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,- 你在背叛我兄弟 -我们走吧 好吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- You're cheatin' on my boy. - Let's go. Okay?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.39,0:42:15.86,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,来吧\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Come on.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.84,0:42:29.40,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我不想夹在你跟另一个家伙之间\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I don't want to get between you and another guy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.47,0:42:31.41,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,这样太不爽了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}That's just not cool.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.51,0:42:35.45,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我知道\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.28,0:42:40.81,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我跟Jasper之间跟以前已经不太一样了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Things are different with me and Jasper now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.92,0:42:44.15,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经不再是小孩子了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}We're not little kids anymore.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.39,0:42:49.55,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,有些事是会改变的 对吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}And things change,right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.63,0:42:51.86,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,他知道那些改变吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Does he know they've changed?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.93,0:42:55.99,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在别讲这些了好吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Let's not talk about this right now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.47,0:43:01.93,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我希望我们做一些 Frost说过的那些事\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I wish we could do what Frost says.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.01,0:43:06.67,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,离开地球一小会儿 然后再回来重新开始\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Leave Earth for a while and come back and begin all over.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.31,0:43:14.27,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,.那样真好 - 是很好\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- It would be so nice. - Nice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.35,0:43:16.62,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,Nice.很美好\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Nice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.50,0:43:30.66,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,- 你在做什么- 离开地球一小会儿\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- What you doin'? - Getting away for a while.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.44,0:43:35.20,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,-这里是佛罗里达 -你说什么是佛罗里达州\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- Florida. - What's Florida?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.27,0:43:38.44,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,- 你的最南端 -嗯哼\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- The southernmost tip of you. - Mm-hmm.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.35,0:43:44.28,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,嗯嗯\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Mmm.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.02,0:43:50.21,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,佛罗里达州好痒啊\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Florida tickles.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.29,0:43:54.75,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,-我们就一路向北 好吗 -好的\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- Then let's move north,shall we? - All right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.86,0:43:58.80,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,到了佐治亚州的桃子林\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Got Georgia peaches.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.80,0:44:07.10,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,还有南加利福尼亚\N{\fscx070\fscy070}And South Carolina.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.17,0:44:10.11,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,一个美丽的州\N{\fscx070\fscy070}A very beautiful state.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.84,0:44:15.61,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,这里是北加利福尼亚\N{\fscx070\fscy070}This is North Carolina.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.22,0:44:22.65,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我走得更北了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I move further north,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.72,0:44:24.75,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我发现了马里兰州\N{\fscx070\fscy070}and I find Maryland.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.26,0:44:32.92,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,嗯嗯\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Mmm.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.00,0:44:36.99,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,-看起来马里兰州也痒了 -我想是的\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- Seems Maryland tickles too. - I think so.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.80,0:44:44.17,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,-我想这里是纽约 -嗯\N{\fscx070\fscy070}- I suppose that one there's New York. - Mmm.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.24,0:44:47.70,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,这里是泽西州 那里是纽约\N{\fscx070\fscy070}That's Jersey. That's New York.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.52,0:44:54.25,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,要拜访一下吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Planning a visit?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.32,0:44:56.79,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,不了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.85,0:44:59.48,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我朝着马萨诸塞出发\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I'm heading towards Massachusetts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.89,0:45:02.83,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,马萨诸塞欢迎你\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Massachusetts welcomes you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.66,0:45:38.59,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,有多糟糕\N{\fscx070\fscy070}How bad is it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.76,0:45:41.70,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,能修好吗\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Is it fixable?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.90,0:45:47.10,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道 挺严重的\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I don't know. It's pretty bad.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.71,0:45:53.94,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我猜你跟Pete谈过了\N{\fscx070\fscy070}Guess you spoke to Pete.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.25,0:45:58.18,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,你在干什么\N{\fscx070\fscy070}What are you doing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.25,0:46:01.01,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道\N{\fscx070\fscy070}I don't know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.09,0:46:04.49,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,那个家伙走进这个小镇 说了一些话\N{\fscx070\fscy070}This guy walks into town,and he says a few things,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.56,0:46:07.29,*Default,说话人,0000,0000,0000,,会让你产生幻想\N{\fscx070\fscy070}and he makes you think a few things.{\r}
